    dc:title "A revision of the Heatherellidae (Parasitiformes: Mesostigmata) with a new genus and two new species from Australasia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1292201>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1292213>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1292223>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1292219> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1292201>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Heatherella callimaulos walter, 1997, female holotype, dorsum. First pair of tubercles are somewhat concealed. The only marginal seta shown is r1. Two types of pores: 12 pairs large (shaded grey) and ten pairs of smaller pores (unshaded). Platelets behind main dorsal shield not obvious (dotted lines)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1292201/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1292213>
    dc:description "FIGURE 25. Aheatherella mira n. sp. male, dorsum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1292213/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1292223>
    dc:description "FIGURES 34–37. (34) Heatherella acanthocharis walter, 1997, dorsomarginal protuberances, pustules and pores of paratype female (P-s5 pustule; P-s6 pore; P-S1 protuberance), dorsal view of flattened specimen, right side; (35) Aheatherella mira n. sp., dorsomarginal protuberances, pustules and pores of paratype female (P-s5 pustule; P-s6 protuberance with closely associated seta), dorsal view of ventrolateral fragment with broken r-setae, left side; (36) Heatherella osleri n. sp., peritreme of paratype female (ventral view, right peritreme of mite); (37) Aheatherella mira n. sp. peritreme of paratype female (ventral view, left peritreme of mite; sclerotised eXopodal portion of eXopodal-peritrematal shield shaded)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1292223/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1292219>
    dc:description "FIGURES 30–31. Heatherella acanthocharis walter, 1997, scanning electron micrographs. (30) idiosoma, showing sloughed certotegument, scale bar = 100 µm; (31) podonotum, with mostly intact cerotegument (fractured behind setae j3 and laterad z3)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1292219/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

